cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use CoViber, please cite it."
title: "CoViber: A Local-First Memory Engine for LLMs over MCP"
abstract: >-
  CoViber is a local-first, privacy-preserving memory engine that gives any LLM
  continuous personal context via the Model Context Protocol. It maintains a
  cross-source work graph, a multi-signal urgency triage queue, an inference-free
  persona model, and local semantic search — entirely on the user's machine, with
  no cloud egress.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Mishra
    given-names: Punit
version: 0.1.0
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - large language models
  - model context protocol
  - personal knowledge graph
  - local-first
  - privacy
  - retrieval-augmented generation
repository-code: "https://github.com/punitmishra/coviber"
